	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Phila</placeName> <date>March 9th 67</date></p>
				<p>My dear <addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Well&#44; you are a<lb/> pretty man&#59; why do you<lb/> not answer my questions&#63;<lb/> Now just read over all<lb/> my letter to <placeName>Savannah</placeName> &#38; <lb/> answer all my questions<lb/> particularly regarding<lb/> <persName>Mr. Falke&#39;s<add>&#63;</add></persName> order. <persName>Mrs Levin&#39;s</persName><lb/> Bible had been lettered <persName>Mrs.<lb/> <hi rend="underline">Nathaniel Levin</hi></persName> before your<lb/> letter directing otherwise was<lb/> received&#44; so&#44; it cannot be<lb/> altered now&#59; you should<lb/> be more particular about</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p><sic>about</sic> these things.</p>
				<p>Now as I regard her <persName>Moises&#39;s</persName><lb/> meditations &#38; prayers&#44; &#8212; first<lb/> you directed that <persName>Burlack<add>&#63;</add></persName><lb/> should send him one&#59; this<lb/> was done&#59; the you directed<lb/> me to send him four medita&#45;<lb/>tions &#38; Prayers&#44; but I sent<lb/> only <hi rend="underline">three</hi> of course&#59; if he<lb/> wants another I will send<lb/> it to him. As regards<lb/> the book which <persName>Miss Joseph</persName> requires&#44; I know nothing a&#45;<lb/>bout it&#44; as this I did not read<lb/> her letter through &#40;not wishing<lb/> to pry into other people&#39;s<lb/> love affairs sharing enough<lb/> to do&#44; to take care of <hi rend="underline">his own</hi>.&#41;<lb/> so please let me know what</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>books she wishes&#44; &#38; it shall<lb/> be sent around to <persName>Mr  Moses</persName>.<lb/> The Occident is out at last&#59;<lb/> some of <persName>Jones</persName> machinery broke<lb/> down &#38; delayed it for a<lb/> day or so&#59; Mamma &#38; I did<lb/> the work up quickly&#59; she<lb/> pasted &#38; I directed &#38; the<lb/> work was all done up in<lb/> less than 2 &#189; hours.</p>
				<p>We have  received a letter from<lb/> <persName>Uncle Sam</persName>&#59; he views the action<lb/> of Congregation the darkest<lb/> light &#38; seems to announce all<lb/> hope&#59; <hi rend="underline">do not mention this I</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">beg</hi>&#59; stop at <placeName>Mobile</placeName><add>&#63;</add> if poss&#45;<lb/>ible on your <add>&#63;</add>&#59; at least<lb/> write to them &#38;  let <hi rend="underline">them know</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">where you are</hi> &#40;<hi rend="underline">entre nous<add>&#63;</add></hi>.&#41;<lb/> Very few books have been sold</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>since you left&#59; <persName>Mr Hayes</persName><lb/> bought a plain prayer book  <persName>Mr. Gutheim</persName> has sent a check<lb/> for &#36;82. &#38; <persName>Dovale</persName> has sent &#36;59<lb/> from <persName>Mr. De Casseres</persName>&#59; I will<lb/> acknowledge receipt of both<lb/> tomorrow &#8212; The girls were<lb/> here this afternoon&#44; they go<lb/> to <persName>Levin&#39;s</persName> on <date>Sunday</date>&#44; Mamma<lb/> has purchased beautiful dress&#45;<lb/>es  for them. Let us know<lb/> how your health is when you<lb/> next write. Mamma has a<lb/> terrible cold &#38;  is feeling very<lb/> miserable indeed&#59; we are kept<lb/> continually busy attending to<lb/> your affairs. The girls tell us<lb/> that  <persName>Mr A J. Jones</persName> wrote to you<lb/> telling you not to come home<lb/> until you have recovered.</p>
				<p>We all send love to you &#38;  hope<lb/> that you will write soon.</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">Yours&#44; <persName role="author">E L Cozens</persName></p>
		</body>
